OL,3,CJail for knife-wielding man who was
OL,4,Ctackled to the floor by shoppers
OL,6,FAvon and Somerset Police officer in
OL,7,Fthe case DC Carl Spicer said: "The
OL,8,Fattack on Tuesday 28 May was stopped
OL,9,Fby the brave actions of members of the
OL,10,Fpublic who threw items at McInally and
OL,11,Ftackled him to the floor, disarming
OL,12,Fhim and detaining him until police
OL,13,Farrived.
OL,15,F"Staff from Bristol Outreach for
OL,16,FHomeless and a PCSO acted quickly and
OL,17,Futilised a bleed kit and provided
OL,18,Ffirst aid to the victim.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/7
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
