OL,3,CJail for knife-wielding man who was
OL,4,Ctackled to the floor by shoppers
OL,6,F"I am confident that the brave actions
OL,7,Fof the public and the steps taken to
OL,8,Fadminister first aid and utilise the
OL,9,Fnearby bleed kit, saved the victim's
OL,10,Flife."
OL,12,FThe court heard how, at around
OL,13,F11.30am, officers received a number of
OL,14,Fcalls reporting an argument between
OL,15,Ftwo men on Bond Street.
OL,17,FMcInally drew a knife from his bag and
OL,18,Fstabbed the victim repeatedly as he
OL,19,Fwas trying to walk away, before head-
OL,20,Fbutting him four times when he tried
OL,21,Fto disarm him.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/7
